                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.937/12: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-19T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 19, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. Hankow despatch No. 585, December 5,<note n="24" xml:id="d810fn24">Not
                        printed.</note> regarding reported increases in export and import duties to
                    be effective January 1. Werner G. Smith Company, Cleveland, Ohio, has
                    telegraphed Department of Commerce as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Chinese Government at Hankow very suddenly imposing heavy tax on export
                            of China wood oil without due notice. This action very unfair to us as
                            American exporters of this commodity as we have sold for delivery in
                            this country not calculating this unfair tax. May we suggest that you
                            attempt to influence the Chinese government to postpone this action
                            until we have had a chance to get our purchases out of China to cover
                            American sales.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Please investigate and if facts warrant it take such action on behalf of Smith
                    Company as appears proper and practicable. Report by telegraph facts in case and
                    action taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
